'''高级长期威胁'''（{{lang-en|advanced persistent threat}}，缩写：'''APT'''），又称'''高级持续性威胁'''、'''先进持续性威胁'''等，是指隐匿而持久的[[黑客_(计算机安全)|电脑入侵]]过程，通常由某些人员精心策划，针对特定的目标。其通常是出于商业或政治动机，针对特定组织或国家，并要求在长时间内保持高隐蔽性。高级长期威胁包含三个要素：高级、长期、威胁。高级强调的是使用复杂精密的恶意软件及技术以利用系统中的漏洞。长期暗指某个外部力量会持续监控特定目标，并从其获取数据。威胁则指人为参与策划的攻击。<ref name="academia.edu">https://www.cademia.edu/6309905/Advanced_Persistent_Threat_-_APT{{dead link|date=2018年5月 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>

APT发起方，如[[政府|政府]]，通常具备持久而有效地针对特定主体的能力及意图。此术语一般指[[互联网|网络]]威胁，尤其是指使用众多情报收集技术来获取敏感信息的网络间谍活动，<ref name="Dell SecureWorks">{{cite web|title=Anatomy of an Advanced Persistent Threat (APT)|url=http://go.secureworks.com/advancedthreats|publisher=Dell SecureWorks|accessdate=2012-05-21|archive-date=2012-07-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120712132139/http://go.secureworks.com/advancedthreats|dead-url=no}}</ref>但也适用于传统的间谍活动之类的威胁。<ref name="Command Five Pty Ltd">{{cite web|title=Are you being targeted by an Advanced Persistent Threat?|url=http://www.commandfive.com/apt.html|publisher=Command Five Pty Ltd|accessdate=2011-03-31|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110406182451/http://www.commandfive.com/apt.html|archivedate=2011年4月6日|df=}}</ref>其他攻击面包括受感染的媒介、入侵供应链、社会工程学。个人，如个人黑客，通常不被称作APT，因为即使个人有意攻击特定目标，他们也通常不具备高级和长期这两个条件。<ref name="commandfive.com">{{cite web|title=The changing threat environment ...|url=http://www.commandfive.com/threats.html|publisher=Command Five Pty Ltd|accessdate=2011-03-31|archive-date=2012-07-24|archive-url=https://archive.is/20120724104653/http://www.commandfive.com/threats.html|dead-url=yes}}</ref>

==历史==
2005年时，英国及美国的一些[[计算机应急响应小组|计算机应急响应组织]]发布报告，提醒人们注意某些针对性的钓鱼电子邮件会释放木马，外泄敏感信息，但「APT」一词还未被使用。<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.lockheedmartin.com/content/dam/lockheed/data/corporate/documents/LM-White-Paper-Intel-Driven-Defense.pdf | title=Intelligence-Driven Computer Network Defense Informed by Analysis of Adversary Campaigns and Intrusion Kill Chains | publisher=Lockheed Martin Corporation Abstract | accessdate=March 13, 2013 | author=Eric M. Hutchins, Michael J. Clopperty, Rohan M. Amin, Ph.D. | archive-date=2015-02-05 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150205103000/http://www.lockheedmartin.com/content/dam/lockheed/data/corporate/documents/LM-White-Paper-Intel-Driven-Defense.pdf | dead-url=no }}</ref>普遍认为「高级长期威胁」这个术语是在2006年由美国空军创造，<ref>{{cite web|title=Assessing Outbound Traffic to Uncover Advanced Persistent Threat|url=http://www.sans.edu/student-files/projects/JWP-Binde-McRee-OConnor.pdf|publisher=SANS Technology Institute|accessdate=2013-04-14|archive-date=2013-02-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130224142242/http://www.sans.edu/student-files/projects/JWP-Binde-McRee-OConnor.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>而格雷格·拉特雷上校一般被认为是该术语的发明人。<ref>{{cite web|title=Introducing Forrester's Cyber Threat Intelligence Research|url=http://blogs.forrester.com/rick_holland/13-02-14-introducing_forresters_cyber_threat_intelligence_research|publisher=Forrester Research|accessdate=2014-04-14|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140415054512/http://blogs.forrester.com/rick_holland/13-02-14-introducing_forresters_cyber_threat_intelligence_research|archivedate=2014-04-15}}</ref>

[[震网|震网]][[电脑蠕虫|蠕虫]]是APT的一个例子，此蠕虫专门针对[[伊朗核问题|伊朗核设施]]的电脑硬件。此事件中，伊朗政府可能就把震网蠕虫的创造者视为一个高级长期威胁。

在[[计算机安全|计算机安全]]社群及媒体中，此术语常指针对政府、公司、政治活跃分子的长期而复杂的[[黑客|黑客]]攻击，也指发起这些攻击幕后团体的活動特徵。日趋频繁的高级长期威胁（APT）可能会逐渐只用于指代计算机黑客入侵。据《PC World》杂志统计，从2010年到2011年，针对性的高级电脑黑客攻击增长了81%。<ref>{{cite web|last=Olavsrud|first=Thor|title=Targeted Attacks Increased, Became More Diverse in 2011|url=http://www.pcworld.com/printable/article/id,254730/printable.html|publisher=PCWorld|accessdate=2015-01-22|archive-date=2019-04-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190410174514/https://www.pcworld.com/printable/article/id,254730/printable.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

对于APT的一个常见误解{{Who|date=May 2011}}是，APT仅仅针对西方政府。虽然针对西方政府的APT事件在西方广为流传，但许多国家的黑客也会通过[[网络空间|网络空间]]收集个人或一群个人的情报。<ref>{{cite web|title=An Evolving Crisis|url=http://www.businessweek.com/magazine/content/08_16/b4080032220668.htm|publisher=BusinessWeek|date=April 10, 2008|accessdate=2010-01-20|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100110120647/http://www.businessweek.com/magazine/content/08_16/b4080032220668.htm|archivedate=2010-01-10|deadurl=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=The New E-spionage Threat|url=http://www.businessweek.com/magazine/content/08_16/b4080032218430.htm|publisher=BusinessWeek|date=April 10, 2008|accessdate=2011-03-19|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110418080952/http://www.businessweek.com/magazine/content/08_16/b4080032218430.htm|archivedate=2011-04-18|deadurl=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Google Under Attack: The High Cost of Doing Business in China|url=http://www.spiegel.de/international/world/0,1518,672742,00.html|publisher=Der Spiegel|date=2010-01-19|accessdate=2010-01-20|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100121005238/http://www.spiegel.de/international/world/0,1518,672742,00.html|archivedate=2010-01-21|deadurl=no}}</ref>[[美国网战司令部|美国网战司令部]]负责协调美国军方对[[网络攻击|网络攻击]]作出的响应。

有说法称一些APT团体直属于或受雇于[[民族国家|民族国家]]。<ref>{{cite web|title=Under Cyberthreat: Defense Contractors|url=http://www.businessweek.com/technology/content/jul2009/tc2009076_873512.htm|publisher=BusinessWeek|date=July 6, 2009|accessdate=2010-01-20|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100111174243/http://www.businessweek.com/technology/content/jul2009/tc2009076_873512.htm|archivedate=2010-01-11|deadurl=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Understanding the Advanced Persistent Threat|url=http://tominfosec.blogspot.com/2010/02/understanding-apt.html|publisher=Tom Parker|date=February 4, 2010|accessdate=2010-02-04|archive-date=2010-02-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100218143530/http://tominfosec.blogspot.com/2010/02/understanding-apt.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Advanced Persistent Threat (or Informationized Force Operations)|url=http://www.usenix.org/event/lisa09/tech/slides/daly.pdf|publisher=Usenix, Michael K. Daly|date=November 4, 2009|accessdate=2009-11-04|archive-date=2011-05-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110513204134/http://www.usenix.org/event/lisa09/tech/slides/daly.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>
掌握大量可辨识的个人身份信息的行业极有可能遭受高级长期威胁，如：<ref name="Dell SecureWorks"/>

*高等教育<ref>{{cite web|last=Ingerman|first=Bret|title=Top-Ten IT Issues, 2011|url=http://www.educause.edu/ero/article/top-ten-it-issues-2011|publisher=Educause Review|accessdate=2015-01-22|archive-date=2015-04-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150407205021/http://www.educause.edu/ero/article/top-ten-it-issues-2011|dead-url=no}}</ref>
